## Auth Flow

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant U as User
    participant FE as React Frontend
    participant BE as Express Backend
    participant SB as Supabase

    U->>FE: Fill registration form
    FE->>BE: POST /api/auth/send-otp
    BE-->>FE: OTP (logged to console)
    U->>FE: Enter OTP
    FE->>BE: POST /api/auth/register
    BE->>SB: INSERT into users
    BE-->>FE: JWT token + user data
    FE->>FE: Store in localStorage

    U->>FE: Click Login
    FE->>BE: POST /api/auth/login
    BE->>SB: SELECT from users
    BE-->>FE: JWT token + user data
    FE->>FE: Store in localStorage, show dashboard
```

## Steps to Go Live

1. **Set up Supabase**: Create project → Run [supabase_schema.sql](file:///c:/Users/asus/Code_folder/Project_code/Festiverse26/festiverse-backend/supabase_schema.sql) → Create `assets` storage bucket (public)
2. **Update [.env](file:///c:/Users/asus/Code_folder/Project_code/Festiverse26/festiverse-backend/.env)** in `festiverse-backend/` with your Supabase URL and Service Role Key
3. **Start backend**: `npm run dev` in `festiverse-backend/`
4. **Restart frontend**: Stop and re-run `npm run dev` in `fesstiverse/` (to pick up [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/asus/Code_folder/Project_code/Festiverse26/fesstiverse/.env.local))

